



### Lloyd Wolf chili

* 1 large can tomatoes
* 1 can tomato sauce (2/3 of large can)
* 3 lb ground chuck, cut for chili
* 1/2 onion, chopped
* 1 can plain rotel
* 1.5 pkg williams chili seasoning
* 2 cans ranch style pinto beans [weight / size??]

* brown meat and onion in oil
* drain; add tomatoes, juice, rotel, onion soup
* boil on low for 30 minutes
* add chili seasoning + pinto beans
* simmer for 15 minutes
* serve with cheddar cheese, sour cream, fritos



